<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-229-036  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 229 036.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  April 17 1989 v6 n15 p31(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Pair of fiber-optic controllers can operate 1 km from host. (TheLogic Co. introduces the BCU-1000 and BCQ-1000) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gyrgo, Gene.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   The Logical Co. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Logical BCU-1000 (Control board) (product introduction)Logical BCQ-1000 (Control board) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Fiber OpticsControllersBoards-CardsProduct IntroductionCompatible HardwareBus Extenders.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Pair of Fiber-Optic Controllers Can Operate 1 km from HostandM;COTTAGE GROVE, Ore.andP;  -- The Logical Co. has introduced a pair of low-cost,fiber-optic controllers for Q-bus and Unibus systems that can be set up andoperated from as far away as 1 kilometer from the host system.andM;The products--the BCU-1000, a Unibus-compatible controller, and the BCQ-1000,a Q-bus-compatible controller--are for use on MicroVAXes and Micro/PDP11s.andO;They are designed to repeat, extend or convert the host system's bus.andP;  Theycan extend the distance a controller can be from the physical bus beyond 50feet.andM;&quot;We felt that it was the right time to offer fiber-optic technology,&quot; aLogical spokesman said.andP;  The controllers are designed to eliminate unwantedsignals as well as problems with ground differentials, lightning anddistance.andM;The controllers do not require additional software or adjustments to existingsoftware.andP;  The models come with I/O panels for access to fiber-optic cables,and on-board LED displays that give status reports on the fiber-optic cableand activity on the bus.andM;The units provide socketed resistor modules that provide bus termination aswell as an address map and limit scheme that reconciles dissimilarbus-address configurations.andM;According to the spokesman, one main attraction is that fiber-optic cable islight, pliable and easy to use&quot; &quot;From a user's point of view, it's mucheasier to use than a typical wire-based cable.&quot;andM;The BCU-1000 and BCQ-1000 also give the bus additional drive capability,company officials said.andP;  The fiber-optic controllers literally extends busesbeyond the typical 50-foot limit to distances as far away as 1 kilometer.andO;The fiber-optic technology, which conforms to Federal CommunicationsCommission regulations, can allow equipment to reside in separate buildngs.andM;The new controllers also provide bus conversion between Q-bus and Unibussystems.andP;  With the controllers, memory and I/O devices on one of the bustypes can be controlled by the other.andM;Only one bus can perform bus arbitration; the controllers are not intendedfor use in interprocessor applications, officials said.andM;Each controller is priced at $1,295 and is available now.andM;The Logical Co. can be contacted at 31225 Lorane Road, Cottage Grove, OR97424, (503) 942-3610.andO;</TEXT></DOC>